title: For Sale/Trade:  Remington 552 Speedmaster .22
postcontent:
For sale or trade today I have a classic Remington 552 Speedmaster chambered for 22 longrifle/long/short. This neat semi-auto plinker will make a great gun for a new shooter, someone looking to burn some ammo, or that person who is nostalgic for a gun from their youth. It is especially cool since the charging handle is located on the left side of the reciever, something that is fairly unusual in American guns. 
 
The rifle is in overall good shape. The blue on the steel parts is near 95%, while there is a bit of minor discoloration on the factory paint on the receiver as well as a few scrapes (the worst shown in picture 3). The wood has some dings and dents from regular use, but nothing that will affect performance or ruin the aesthetics. The only part it is missing is the shell deflector and the associated screws, but that should not impact function in any way. Overall a gun with an honest amount of wear but no serious abuse. 
 
This is definitely a neat little rifle and the new owner will surely have tons of fun with it!
